ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: During weeknights (Sunday through Thursday nights only) for the past month, how often did your child perform the same activities in the hour before going to bed (for example, bathe, brush teeth, read/listen to story, listen to music)?

During weeknights (Sunday through Thursday nights only) for the past month, how often did your child perform activities in the same order before going to bed (for example, bathe, brush teeth, read/listen to story, go to bed)?
During weeknights (Sunday through Thursday nights only) for the past month, how often did your child sleep in the same place (for example, in his/her bed, in parents bed, on couch)?
During weeknights (Sunday through Thursday nights only) for the past month, how often did your child go to bed at the same time (within 10 minutes)?
During weeknights (Sunday through Thursday nights only) for the past month, how often did your child get put to bed by the same person?

During weekends (Friday and Saturday nights) for the past month, how often did your child perform the same activities in the hour before going to bed (for example, bathe, brush teeth, read/listen to story, listen to music)?

During weekends (Friday and Saturday nights) for the past month, how often did your child go to bed at the same time (within 10 minutes)?
During weekends (Friday and Saturday nights) for the past month, how often did your child get put to bed by the same person?
How upset does your child get if he or she does not perform the same activities in the hour before going to bed (for example, bathe, brush teeth, read/listen to story, listen to music)?
How upset does your child get if he or she does not perform activities in the same order before going to bed (for example, bathe, brush teeth, read/listen to story, go to bed)?
How upset does your child get if he or she does not sleep in the same place (for example, in his/her bed, in parents bed, on couch)?
How upset does your child get if he or she does not go to bed at the same time (within 10 minutes)?
How upset does your child get if he or she does not get put to bed by the same person?
